Known for their dry aged rib eye (15 or 30 day). Apparently the only place on the island who dry ages in-house. Beef is cornfed from the mainland. The explanation was that the fattier cornfed beef works better for keeping moisture throughout the dry aging. The dry aging adds an interesting  flavor while also making the steak more tender. Nothing amazing as far as sides but the steak is a good value. Order the tempura ice cream for dessert (they'll bring it from the Sansei side). Lots of wine options. Great service. Three hours free validated parking in the Marriott parking.
